                            <comment id="16972906" author="dschlenkc1" created="Tue, 12 Nov 2019 23:38:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=acosentino&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;acosentino&quot;&gt;acosentino&lt;/a&gt; thanks for responding! I&apos;ve tested this change against the v2 branch IRL and it does fix the issue. I tried my hand at figuring out how to write a unit test, but I couldn&apos;t figure out how to either obtain the underlying LoggingFeature from the CxfEndpoint to check for its value or successfully intercept the output to brute force testing that a message longer than the default worked. Happy to add one if someone can point me in the right direction, though. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/3332&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;PR #3332&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
